Package com.sap.conn.jco.ms

Contains all interfaces of JCo related to system information queries.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    JCoApplicationServer
    Contains technical information about an application server of an ABAP system.
    JCoLogonGroup
    Represents a logon group of an ABAP system.
    JCoMessageServer
    The JCoMessageServer interface is the entry point for accessing the technical information of an ABAP system.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    JCoMessageServerFactory
    The factory class allows to retrieve a JCoMessageServer instance.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    MessageServerQueryException
    A MessageServerQueryException will be thrown, when querying the message server for information is failing.

Package com.sap.conn.jco.ms Description

Contains all interfaces of JCo related to system information queries. With the JCoMessageServerFactory it is possible to lookup a JCoMessageServer, which provides information about itself and the system, including the list of available JCoLogonGroups and the list of JCoApplicationServers belonging to the system. This data is useful for wizards that shall be used for the configuration of destinations.

Note:
The implementations for all interfaces in this package are exclusively provided by the JCo runtime. Custom interface implementations are not supported. Hence, adding a new method to any interface in this package is not considered as an incompatible change.
